OL,3,CNoel Clarke set to learn outcome of
OL,4,Clibel claim against Guardian publisher
OL,6,FGavin Millar KC, for GNM, said there
OL,7,Fis "not a shred of evidence" to
OL,8,Fsupport Clarke's claim of a
OL,9,Fconspiracy, describing it as
OL,10,F"nonsensical and rather desperate
OL,11,Fspeculation".
OL,13,FHe said Clarke has a "very clear
OL,14,Fmotive to lie" because he "stands to
OL,15,Flose a great deal".
OL,17,FIn written submissions, Mr Millar said
OL,18,FClarke "used his power to prey on and
OL,19,Fharass female colleagues" over a
OL,20,Fperiod of 15 years.
